{
  "texts": [
    "Some added that delivery services enable them to eat more frequently, suggesting increased daily food intake.",
    "These insights reflect a group of users who view food delivery as a tool that can support efficient and potentially healthier lifestyle habits when used intentionally.",
    "Source: Survey Data Table 19 summarizes the thematic coding across all participant responses regarding the perceived health impact of food delivery services.",
    "The theme of Negative Health Perceptions had the highest frequency, with six distinct nodes and 20 coded responses, indicating that concerns about nutritional quality, weight gain, and food safety were dominant among respondents.",
    "In contrast, the Neutral / Agency Perspectives theme included four nodes and six responses, reflecting a smaller group that acknowledged potential impacts but emphasized personal responsibility and choice in mitigating adverse effects."
  ]
}